  ('423b36db-a390-4f86-b215-80327a66e06f', 'Write 2-3 sentences expressing your opinion about learning French. Why do you study it? What do you find challenging or enjoyable?', NULL, '{}'::text[], 'personal_expression', 'advanced', 'open_ended', 'Advanced personal expression requiring opinion statements, reasons, and complex sentence structures', '{"Use phrases like ''je pense que'', ''je trouve que'', ''parce que''","Include both positive and challenging aspects","Use connectors like ''mais'', ''et'', ''donc''"}'::text[], TRUE, NULL, '2026-02-01T09:13:02.750401+00:00', '2026-02-01T09:13:02.750401+00:00'),
  ('e426e01c-c9bd-4bba-85ad-54d172215874', 'How do you say ''thank you'' in French?', 'merci', '{"merci beaucoup","je vous remercie","je te remercie"}'::text[], 'greetings', 'beginner', 'translation', 'Basic expression of gratitude in French', '{"This is one of the first words most people learn in French","It sounds similar to the English word ''mercy''"}'::text[], FALSE, NULL, '2026-02-01T09:13:02.750401+00:00', '2026-02-01T09:13:02.750401+00:00'),
  ('54d6f621-7018-4662-a563-40e9d65f6cd5', 'Conjugate the verb ''être'' (to be) in the present tense for ''nous'' (we)', 'nous sommes', '{"sommes"}'::text[], 'verb_conjugation:être', 'beginner', 'conjugation', 'The verb ''être'' is irregular and must be memorized. ''Nous sommes'' means ''we are''', '{"The conjugation starts with ''s''","Think of the English word ''sum'' - it sounds similar"}'::text[], FALSE, NULL, '2026-02-01T09:13:02.750401+00:00', '2026-02-01T09:13:02.750401+00:00'),
  ('b699954d-eb44-4e42-882b-9cfd26d22961', 'How do you say ''I have a cat'' in French?', 'J''ai un chat', '{"J''ai un chat.","Je ai un chat"}'::text[], 'verb_conjugation:avoir', 'beginner', 'translation', 'Uses the verb ''avoir'' (to have) in first person singular with the masculine noun ''chat''', '{"Use the verb ''avoir'' conjugated for ''I''","''Cat'' in French is ''chat'' (masculine)","Remember the contraction j''ai"}'::text[], TRUE, NULL, '2026-02-01T09:13:02.750401+00:00', '2026-02-01T09:13:02.750401+00:00'),
  ('350d43bd-1aa2-4dc1-b256-9dc5462a4a40', 'Conjugate the regular -er verb ''parler'' (to speak) in the present tense for ''tu'' (you informal)', 'tu parles', '{"parles"}'::text[], 'verb_conjugation:-er_verbs', 'beginner', 'conjugation', 'Regular -er verbs follow a pattern: remove -er and add endings. For ''tu'', add -es', '{"Remove the -er ending and add the ''tu'' ending","The ''tu'' ending for -er verbs is -es","The final ''s'' is silent"}'::text[], FALSE, NULL, '2026-02-01T09:13:02.750401+00:00', '2026-02-01T09:13:02.750401+00:00'),
  ('b29d16df-8e44-421c-a400-7d362369f14b', 'Translate: I eat breakfast at 7 o''clock in the morning.', 'Je prends le petit-déjeuner à sept heures du matin.', '{"Je mange le petit-déjeuner à sept heures du matin.","Je prends mon petit-déjeuner à 7h du matin.","Je déjeune à sept heures du matin."}'::text[], 'daily_routine', 'intermediate', 'translation', 'Combines time expressions with daily routine vocabulary. ''Prendre'' or ''manger'' can be used for eating meals', '{"''Breakfast'' is ''le petit-déjeuner'' in French","Use ''à'' before the time","The verb ''prendre'' (to take) is commonly used with meals"}'::text[], TRUE, NULL, '2026-02-01T09:13:02.750401+00:00', '2026-02-01T09:13:02.750401+00:00'),
  ('9dfe2b8b-efb4-484b-8742-75da6a19b962', 'How do you ask someone ''What is your name?'' in French (formal)?', 'Comment vous appelez-vous?', '{"Quel est votre nom?","Comment est-ce que vous vous appelez?"}'::text[], 'question_formation', 'intermediate', 'question_formation', 'Formal question using the reflexive verb ''s''appeler'' with inversion or using ''quel est''', '{"The verb ''s''appeler'' means ''to call oneself''","Use ''vous'' for formal address","Inversion is common in formal questions"}'::text[], TRUE, NULL, '2026-02-01T09:13:02.750401+00:00', '2026-02-01T09:13:02.750401+00:00'),
  ('63110bd9-8d62-4ba2-a827-ff8c3fdddcc0', 'Describe your favorite food and explain why you like it. Write 2-3 sentences in French.', NULL, '{}'::text[], 'food', 'intermediate', 'open_ended', 'Practice expressing food preferences and giving reasons using opinion phrases and descriptive vocabulary', '{"Start with ''Mon plat préféré est...'' or ''J''adore...''","Use ''parce que'' (because) to explain why","Include adjectives like ''délicieux'', ''bon'', ''savoureux''"}'::text[], TRUE, NULL, '2026-02-01T09:13:02.750401+00:00', '2026-02-01T09:13:02.750401+00:00'),
  ('c601091d-b756-4e13-a03f-2d67c7ddd6c9', 'Write a sentence using the verb ''faire'' (to do/make) in the present tense, describing what you do on weekends.', NULL, '{}'::text[], 'daily_routine', 'advanced', 'sentence_building', 'Practice using the irregular verb ''faire'' in context with weekend activities and time expressions', '{"''Faire'' is irregular: je fais, tu fais, il/elle fait, nous faisons, vous faites, ils/elles font","Common expressions: faire du sport, faire les courses, faire la cuisine","Use ''le week-end'' or ''le samedi/dimanche''"}'::text[], TRUE, NULL, '2026-02-01T09:13:02.750401+00:00', '2026-02-01T09:13:02.750401+00:00'),
  ('920eb4d7-42e2-4cb7-ae43-ef410ac4c3a0', 'Describe a person you admire using at least 3 adjectives and explain why you admire them. Write 2-3 sentences in French.', NULL, '{}'::text[], 'describing_people', 'advanced', 'open_ended', 'Practice descriptive adjectives with proper gender agreement and expressing opinions with supporting reasons', '{"Remember adjective agreement (masculine/feminine)","Useful adjectives: intelligent(e), gentil(le), courageux/courageuse, créatif/créative","Use ''Je l''admire parce que...'' to explain"}'::text[], TRUE, NULL, '2026-02-01T09:13:02.750401+00:00', '2026-02-01T09:13:02.750401+00:00'),
  ('88734183-b7b5-476b-8915-f7f677ba9810', 'Write 2-3 sentences comparing two places you have visited using comparative structures (plus...que, moins...que, aussi...que).', NULL, '{}'::text[], 'describing_places', 'advanced', 'sentence_building', 'Practice comparative structures with descriptive vocabulary for places, requiring complex sentence construction', '{"Use ''plus...que'' (more...than), ''moins...que'' (less...than), ''aussi...que'' (as...as)","Past tense ''j''ai visité'' or ''je suis allé(e)'' can introduce the places","Compare aspects like: grand (big), beau (beautiful), intéressant (interesting), animé (lively)"}'::text[], TRUE, NULL, '2026-02-01T09:13:02.750401+00:00', '2026-02-01T09:13:02.750401+00:00')
